[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello everyone,</p>\n<p>I was building Linux Kernel in Fedora 43 today, I followed the below steps and It \"worked\" in terms that it didn't panic and I have limited access to some commands like ls, nano, etc, but I cannot do a touch, etc ...</p>\n<p>I wonder if those steps make sense and if I'm missing something important. I used ChatGPT in some scenarios to troubleshoot some issues I had.</p>\n<p>Install Rust and Dependencies</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>rust<span class=\"w\"> </span>rust-src<span class=\"w\"> </span>bindgen-cli<span class=\"w\"> </span>rustfmt<span class=\"w\"> </span>clippy\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Clone the Kernel</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>git<span class=\"w\"> </span>clone<span class=\"w\"> </span>git@github.com:Rust-for-Linux/linux.git\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>make<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>rustavailable\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install <code>flex</code> (and other Kconfig build deps)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>flex<span class=\"w\"> </span>bison<span class=\"w\"> </span>ncurses-devel\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install the full LLVM toolchain</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>clang<span class=\"w\"> </span>lld<span class=\"w\"> </span>llvm<span class=\"w\"> </span>llvm-devel\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install elfutils development package</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>elfutils-libelf-devel\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install OpenSSL development package</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>openssl-devel\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install QEMU</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>qemu-system-x86\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Install busybox</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>sudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>dnf<span class=\"w\"> </span>install<span class=\"w\"> </span>busybox\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Setup Kernel Configuration</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>make<span class=\"w\"> </span>menuconfig\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>a) Go to <em>General setup → Rust support (CONFIG_RUST)</em>, enable it. </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>General setup →\n    [*] Rust support (CONFIG_RUST)\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>b) Then under <em>Kernel hacking → Sample kernel code → Rust samples</em>, enable some sample modules</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>make<span class=\"w\"> </span>rust-analyzer\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It should output:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>rust-project.json\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Build the kernel full</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>make<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-j<span class=\"k\">$(</span>nproc<span class=\"k\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It should output:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>Kernel: arch/x86/boot/bzImage is ready  (#1)\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Create a clean minimal rootfs with BusyBox</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"ch\">#!/usr/bin/env bash</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-e\n<span class=\"c1\"># 1. Remove old rootfs and initramfs</span>\nrm<span class=\"w\"> </span>-rf<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs<span class=\"w\"> </span>initramfs.cpio<span class=\"w\"> </span>initramfs.cpio.gz\n<span class=\"c1\"># 2. Create minimal directory structure</span>\nmkdir<span class=\"w\"> </span>-p<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/<span class=\"o\">{</span>bin,sbin,etc,proc,sys,usr/bin,usr/sbin,dev<span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># 3. Copy BusyBox</span>\ncp<span class=\"w\"> </span>/usr/bin/busybox<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/bin/\nchmod<span class=\"w\"> </span>+x<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/bin/busybox\n<span class=\"c1\"># 4. Create device nodes (required for console)</span>\nsudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>mknod<span class=\"w\"> </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">622</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/dev/console<span class=\"w\"> </span>c<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">5</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">1</span>\nsudo<span class=\"w\"> </span>mknod<span class=\"w\"> </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">666</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/dev/null<span class=\"w\"> </span>c<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"m\">3</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># 5. Create BusyBox symlinks INSIDE /bin</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/bin\n<span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>cmd<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>sh<span class=\"w\"> </span>mount<span class=\"w\"> </span>ls<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">echo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>dmesg<span class=\"w\"> </span>cat<span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span>ln<span class=\"w\"> </span>-sf<span class=\"w\"> </span>busybox<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span><span class=\"nv\">$cmd</span><span class=\"s2\">\"</span>\n<span class=\"k\">done</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-\n<span class=\"c1\"># 6. Create init script</span>\ncat<span class=\"w\"> </span>&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/init<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">&lt;&lt;'EOF'</span>\n<span class=\"s\">#!/bin/sh</span>\n<span class=\"s\">mount -t proc none /proc</span>\n<span class=\"s\">mount -t sysfs none /sys</span>\n<span class=\"s\">echo \"*** Welcome to minimal initramfs! ***\"</span>\n<span class=\"s\">exec /bin/sh</span>\n<span class=\"s\">EOF</span>\nchmod<span class=\"w\"> </span>+x<span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs/init\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Build the initramfs</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>minimal_initramfs\nfind<span class=\"w\"> </span>.<span class=\"w\"> </span>-print0<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>cpio<span class=\"w\"> </span>--null<span class=\"w\"> </span>-ov<span class=\"w\"> </span>--format<span class=\"o\">=</span>newc<span class=\"w\"> </span>&gt;<span class=\"w\"> </span>../initramfs.cpio\n<span class=\"nb\">cd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>..\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Boot custom Linux kernel in QEMU</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>qemu-system-x86_64<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span>2G<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-kernel<span class=\"w\"> </span>arch/x86/boot/bzImage<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-initrd<span class=\"w\"> </span>initramfs.cpio<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-append<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"console=ttyS0 rdinit=/init nokaslr initcall_debug loglevel=8 earlyprintk=ttyS0\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-serial<span class=\"w\"> </span>mon:stdio<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-enable-kvm\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Debug</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"ch\">#!/bin/bash</span>\nqemu-system-x86_64<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-s<span class=\"w\"> </span>-S<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-m<span class=\"w\"> </span>2G<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-kernel<span class=\"w\"> </span>arch/x86/boot/bzImage<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-initrd<span class=\"w\"> </span>initramfs.cpio<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-append<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"console=ttyS0 rdinit=/init nokaslr\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-serial<span class=\"w\"> </span>mon:stdio<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span>-enable-kvm\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Notes for debugging</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>gdb<span class=\"w\"> </span>vmlinux\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>rust-gdb<span class=\"w\"> </span>vmlinux\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>target remote localhost:1234\n</code></pre></div>",
